sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(complaint_id) AS total_complaints
FROM complaint_comments
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT severity_level, COUNT(*) AS complaint_count
FROM complaint_types
GROUP BY severity_level;

SELECT complaint_id, AVG(rating_value) AS average_rating
FROM complaint_ratings
GROUP BY complaint_id;

external_knowledge:
Severity levels are ranked in the following order (from most severe to least severe): Critical, Major, Minor; 
A resolution time greater than zero indicates a valid resolution time; 
Severity level and resolution time are considered key performance indicators for evaluating the effectiveness and efficiency of complaint resolution processes.
